John,<br><br>
It is all very pathetic. Motive for such an attitude toward someone who has risked live and limb at the &quot;order&quot; of this country, and was decorated for his selfless heroism, is beyond rational explanation. <br><br>
I guess it is truly irrational, something difficult for most of us to accept, but a fact of life, none the less.<br><br>
I personally know Ed Ramon, and I am proud to have a friendship with a person who has earned all 76 of his Vietnam War decorations, earned with his blood, sweat, and tears.<br><br>
All I can say is that I pity detractors of this type. They must all lead very small, pathetic, constricted, depressed, and lonely lives.<br><br>
Geepers, I have two Bronze Stars and a decoration from the Republic of Vietnam, and proud of it! I guess I must be screwed up as well! HA!
